description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF LCO;provided children and caregivers with information and knowledge on child protection risks as well as stimulated collective reflection and community-led action.; As part of UNICEF community based support on child protection, the program was able to reach over 167,000;individuals through community based PSS, caregiver program and the Qudwa initiatives. Despite the contextual challenges faced UNICEF;managed to engage with key influencers such as barbers, beauticians and;religious leaders from all confessions through the Qudwa initiatives who have been acting as child rights advocates and agent of change. | Status:Met | As-of Date:08/12/2021
